<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[164,779,466,548]" box="[164,276,466,487]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis box="[164,276,466,487]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[164,779,466,548]" lastBlockId="13.[826,1441,198,342]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Hermatypic, plocoid, generally ramose, rarely massive or encrusting; septa are generally poorly developed and mostly arranged in two cycles; the columella is mostly poorly developed (
<bibRefCitation author="Veron JEN &amp; Pichon M" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refId="ref18447" refString="Veron JEN, Pichon M. 1976. Scleractinia of Eastern Australia. Monograph Series of the Australian Institute for Marine Science I." type="book" year="1976">Veron &amp; Pichon, 1976</bibRefCitation>
), strong tabular endothecal dissepiments. Verrucae are common, although in some species reduced or absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
